node.text:
I haven’t been able to stop crying since I found out I was nominated for the @aiaawards Makeup Influencer of the Year. I will never forget this moment. 

I am so appreciative to all those who nominated me, as well as to those who have voted for me so far. 

If you’d like to vote, the link is here:

https://www.aiaawards.com/vote/

node.text: Join @ashleygraham and I as we discuss the NEW! @sttropeztan Self Tan Ultimate Glow Kit in collaboration with Ashley Graham. My absolute favorite self tanner I have tried so far. The full transformation at the end is EXACTLY why I love it. You can see the results so clearly and how much GLOW my skin has. What an incredible product. Who's tried it? Get it now at @ultabeauty #ashleygraham #sttropez #sttropeztan #sttropezpartner

node.text: As someone who has loved and supported @jaclynhill for over 8 years, I am so proud of her. Watching her growth and success has been so inspiring. You can genuinely see the love and dedication Jaclyn has put into her brand since she first launched it. With each set back, she has risen up and absolutely KILLED IT. Sell out after sell out. I truly believe no one deserves it more. This is what years of hard work looks like. This collection, along with her others, is STUNNING. S T U N N I N G. Not a single complaint. I am impressed beyond words with @jaclynhill and I honestly cannot wait to see what else is to come from @jaclynhillcosmetics. Major congrats on this collection! Definitely get your hands on it when it launches if you can, it is more than worth it.

node.title: Is the new @jaclynhillcosmetics Haute Topic summer collection worth it?

node.text:
This may the prettiest I have ever felt! 

Have you ever tried a full face of one brand? Today I went for @ctilburymakeup because they had gifted me a bunch of products to try! I was BEYOND excited about the result. 

What’s ONE brand that you would love to do a FULL face of? 😳

Here are the products I used in order:

- Magic Serum Crystal Elixir 
- Magic Cream
- Hollywood Flawless Filter (Shade 1 Fair)
- Airbrush Flawless Foundation (Shade 5 Neutral) (I am Shade 1 Neutral when not tanned)
- Magic Away Concealer (Shade 2 Fair) 
- Airbrush Flawless Finish Powder (Shade 1 Fair) 
- Hollywood Contour Wand (Shade Light to Medium)
- Hollywood Light Wand (Shade Pillow Talk, Used as Blush)
- Hollywood Light Wand (Shade Spotlight, Used as Highlighter)
- NEW! Brow Cheat (Shade Medium Brown) 
- NEW! Legendary Brows (Shade Dark Brown)
- Pillow Talk Luxury Palette
- Hollywood Flawless Eye Filter (Limited Edition) 
- Pillow Talk Push Up Lashes Mascara
- Lip Cheat Lip Liner (Shade Foxy Brown) 
- Hot Lips Lipstick (Shade Kim K.w.) 
- Airbrush Flawless Setting Spray

node.text:
I cannot believe that I am standing in a literal dream. If you haven’t been following me long, just last year I was living in a college dorm room confused about where my life was going and uncertain of my future. 

After being told by a professor that following a dream was unrealistic and that I shouldn’t even bother, it set off a fire in me. 

I knew my exact dream and I was prepared to show that professor, and everyone else who ever doubted me, how incredibly wrong they were.

And I did. This week I moved into a dream home that I never would have even imagined in my lifetime. Countless hours of hard work and determination has put me here. Growing up, I have always been a “workaholic” and someone willing to do whatever it takes. The minute I was legally able, I got my first job and took on a second while in high school. I worked four jobs simultaneously while a full time college student. When I saw my potential as a beauty content creator, and that is was truly possible, I told myself I wouldn’t stop fighting for it no matter what. Sometimes I even sacrificed my mental health for hard work. 

And in this moment, I finally feel like I can breathe. I am sitting on the couch in my new home as I write this, taking all of this in and feeling the utmost gratitude for the life I have made for myself. As well as for the support I have received from millions of people every moment as I made my dreams come true. Taking all of you on the entire journey has been the best part. Thank you. 

If I can inspire anyone: if you have a dream, whatever it may be, I promise you it is not “unrealistic.” And the people putting those thoughts into your head, are the people who likely have a dream that they were too afraid to fight for.

❤️🏠

node.text:
People always ask me, “how can you confidently wear that out of the house?” 

So my question back to you is, “why are you so concerned by what others are going to think?” 

Because seriously, who cares? I will wear this look to the grocery store, the post office, the mall, classes at school, literally anything.

Individuality is so powerful. And you will be a happier person when you simply do what YOU want to do. When you allow your creative juices to flow and push yourself in new directions, you start to see life differently.

So wear the purple, blue, pink, and all colors of the rainbow on your eyes if you want to. Do it with confidence. Do it with love and passion. And trust me, you’ll receive plenty of compliments from others. A strange look here or there? Sure. But that’s a reflection of them as a person, not you.

Wearing my Mikayla x @glamlite full collection + @kaima_cosmetics Chameleon flakes. 
💜
